fields.class_description: A Total Body workout using 3 different styles. 4 minutes cardio using Tabata 20/10 followed by strength training and core exercises performed for longer periods to work on form and technique.
fields.class_more_detail:
The foundation to all exercises. A strong core sets the body up to achieve its best results. All classes have core workouts in them whether used in a circuit or a the end of a workout as a cool down. Pilates and yoga exercises will become familiar and modifications are always given to help build at all levels whether it’s for strengthening a weak lower back to performing the same exercise as a power move.
For example:
Level 1: Pelvic Tilts (correctional)
Level 2: Low Crunches
Level 3: Crunches with Legs Raised
Level 4: Sit Ups (weight optional)

fields.class_description: Strength sets focusing on different muscle groups (Total Body, Upper, Lower & Core) broken up by 2 minutes of Cardio

Anything goes. Different techniques are used providing variety. Anything might come up whether it’s a 10 minute Circuit or a 4 min Core AMRAP but whatever it is, it will be challenging, fun and sweaty!
Focusing on Strength & Flexibility. This class may be low impact but it will get you sweating and burning calories. Exercises are slowed down, very specific to balance and core work.
Fast paced and intense. You won’t know what hit you. The hour will fly by.
